    "Research has also highlighted the importance of transparency and interpretability in benchmark results, emphasizing that stakeholders should understand the basis of evaluations to trust and act on them [68]- [71].",
    "This theme reflects a broader move towards more accountable and equitable AI, with benchmarks playing a pivotal role in guiding the development and deployment of fairer models.",
    "D. Ethical Considerations and Societal Impacts of LLM BiasResearch in this theme explores the broader ethical implications and societal impacts of biases in LLMs.",
    "Studies have raised concerns about the potential for biased LLM outputs to reinforce existing social inequalities and undermine efforts towards inclusivity and equity [8], [11], [72].",
